Reasoning: The paper deals with techniques for reducing memory footprint and run-time latency in neural networks, specifically binary neural networks, for image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel learning-based approach for filter-level pruning, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical and experimental comparison between different methods, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to image classification datasets, which could be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
